Diego Costa limped off against Stoke on Saturday with a hamstring injury . 
  The Chelsea striker is likely to be fit to face Arsenal in the Premier League on April 26 . 
  Costa is unlikely to miss the rest of the title run-in and could return within two weeks . 
  The Spain international came on as a substitute in the 2-1 win over Stoke . 
  Costa will miss the games against Manchester United and Arsenal . 
  The striker has identified the Arsenal game as his comeback game . 
